com.protobufel.multikeymap

Interface LiteSetMultimap<K,V>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - the type of Map's key
    V - the type of actual values

    public interface LiteSetMultimap<K,V>
    A lite wrapper of a mutable Map which values are Set of actual values

    • Method Detail

      • clear

        void clear()
        Clears all data

      • remove

        boolean remove(K key,
               V value)
        Finds the record with the specified key and removes the value, if present, from the set of its values. If there are no values left in the set, removes the entire record from the LiteSetMultimap.
        Parameters:
        key - the key to search for
        value - the value to be removed corresponding to the search key
        Returns:
        true if value is removed, false, otherwise

      • size

        int size()
        Gets the number of records in the LiteSetMultimap.
        Returns:
        the size of the the LiteSetMultimap, zero if empty

        Returns:
        the Set of the values corresponding to the search key

      • put

        boolean put(K key,
            V value)
        Adds the value to the set of values corresponding to the search key. If no such record is found, creates a new record with the set initialized to the value.
        Parameters:
        key - the key to search for
        value - the value to add to the set of values corresponding to the search key
        Returns:
        true if value is added, false, otherwise
